main event: Multiple sightings of unidentified aerial objects were reported in Wilmington, Delaware on various dates in 1956, including objects with unusual shapes and movements, such as sudden appearances, rapid darting motions, and disintegration into smaller objects.
interesting points: A radio mathematician flying between Washington D.C. and Philadelphia reported seeing a large, round, stationary bright light, which quickly darted upwards at a steep angle, disappearing in seconds, and was deemed unrelated to any known object.
Witnesses observed a round, shiny, fiery yellow, saucer-shaped object streaking across the sky at incredible speeds before disappearing, with no indication of a conventional aircraft or missile.
A witness observed a peculiar, circular object floating smoothly across the sky at high speed, unlike any conventional aircraft, and estimated its speed to be 300-400 miles per hour.
Descriptions of the sightings included a saucer-shaped object with bright blue-green eyes and a bell-shaped, rotational appearance, causing confusion and amazement among witnesses.

The sightings were observed by multiple credible witnesses, including a radio mathematician, a group of friends, and individuals with no specific expertise, and their reports were included in Project Blue Book records.
sighted object: various unidentified aerial objects with unusual shapes and movements
witnesses: multiple credible witnesses, including a radio mathematician and other observers with varying expertise
photographs: no photographs available in the report
